05/09/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Health Minister Mustafa Xhani and Greek Ambassador Dimitris Iliopoulos signed a two-year agreement Thursday (4 September) on co-operation in the health sector. The document envisions free hospitalisation for 300 Albanians in Greek hospitals during the next year.
In other news Thursday, mountain instructors from the armies of Macedonia and Albania completed a joint course in Demir Kapija, Macedonia. The training is a part of a project to promote regional co-operation in the defence arena. (MPA - 04/09/03)
